ught was love for Ms.Novocaine, and what you were willing to do,but ultimately, everything was exercised andlet out on the plains of New Vegas.Sadja's story is full of twists and turns, goingto dizzying emotional highs before the finalrevelation that brought you to your lowest, tothe point that Ms. Novocaine even askedwhat had made you so upset. Memoria wasshort, and expensive from its asking price,but the game made you despondent overeach character's possible fate.You find yourself snapped out of your dazewhen someone's hand lays itself on yourshoulder. You turn round, only to be greetedwith two lips planting themselves firmly onyour own. Summer-Rain has arrived, andyou feel your spirits soar ever so slightly.""You looked... lost.""She smiles to you,having sneaked into your class. You giveher a terse smile, as you feel a pang ofregret from feeling a sense of longing forMs. Novocaine, based on your memories.""I was.""You start, whispering so thelecturer won't take notice of either of you.""I was thinking of... old memories.""Summer-Rain puts her hand on yours.""Starboy... it's okay. You believe me,don't you?""You nod, this time sure ofboth yourself and the future with thegirl before you, your Summer-Rain.""I do.""MEMORIA."
