,Recommended,243200,16738482,"Posted: 27 June, 2015",all,Ierocis,"Very well done adventure game that harkens back to Sierra's golden age. Beautiful art work, compelling story, the puzzles are logical not arbitrary. There was one game breaking bug near the start that had it crash to desktop after the intro that no one ever seemed to bother to patch. To get around it you have to have the texture compession turned on in the Visionaire Configuration Tool. It will make the game run super slow and you may think it has hung but it is just loading really slowly. Once you're past the intro and opening credits save the game and shut it off again. No further issues came up. Highly recommend this point & click adventure game if you at all like the genre. Note: Some voice acting can be painful at times but it is easily over looked when playing this gem. 2 possible endings but they're basically the same (not counting all the ways to die or fail). Yep, about 10 hours game play if you do pretty much everything.Basically it's a fantasy game set in Germany's most popular RPG (Dark Eye aka Aventuria). You play as Geron, a hero who happens to live in a town of bigots who don't really like him or anyone really. You're trying to have your friend changed back from a raven. In the course of doing this you are asked to solve a riddle that revolves around a princess about 400 years in the past(who you also play as in these flashbacks)."
