76561198074108020,Recommended,243200,30215160,Posted: 27 February,all,pokpo43,"A classic point-and-click adventure game that is entertaining with a captivating story.  I have developed a soft spot for this game developer after playing a few of their other games but this game is very enjoyable and fun to play in a casual pace and setting.  The characters are funny and likable and the dialogues are pretty enjoyable.  It is a bit confusing to follow the storyline in the beginning just because the story hops around between two main protagonists from different time periods but you will soon catch up.  The puzzles and missions are relatively straightforward, but one might fine a few not too intuitive, such as casting vision spell in the correct order so that you can give a ""push"" to have someone do something, which might be frustrating at times, but all in all, very fun.  I also like the fact that this game is not abhorrently long - in fact, it is on the shorter side when it comes to game-length, even though I was a bit sad to see the game ending.I would recommend this game, but probably not at its full price.  Would highly recommend that you grab this jewel when it goes on sale :)"
